{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place all-purpose flour, whole wheat flour, water, baking powder and ¼ tsp salt into mixing bowl and mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>, then knead <nobr>2 min\/<\/nobr>.","Transfer dough to a lightly floured surface. Cut dough in half and shape each piece into a ball. Cover with a damp paper towel and let rest 10 minutes. Meanwhile preheat oven to 425°F and line two baking sheets with parchment. Clean mixing bowl.","Place Parmesan cheese, lemon peel, peppercorns and ¼ tsp salt into mixing bowl and grind <nobr>15 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>.","Add garlic and green onions (white parts only) and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>.","Add ricotta, milk and red pepper flakes and mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 3.5<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Working with one piece of dough at a time, roll out each into an oblong shape (approx. 14 in. x 7 in.). Transfer onto prepared baking sheets and brush with 1 tbsp olive oil. Prebake each flatbread for 10 minutes (425°F). Meanwhile, place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh in squash, zucchini and cherry tomatoes.","Carefully remove baking sheets from oven. Brush flatbreads with remaining 1 tbsp olive oil. Spread each with reserved ricotta mixture, leaving a ¼ inch border. Top with reserved squash, zucchini and tomatoes. Bake for 10-12 minutes (425°F) or until edges are brown. Let rest 3-5 minutes before slicing each flatbread into six pieces. Garnish with reserved onions (green parts, chopped) and serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["8 ½ oz all-purpose flour, plus extra to dust","3 oz whole wheat flour","6 oz water","1 tsp baking powder","½ tsp salt, divided","1 oz Parmesan cheese, cubed","1 lemon, thin peel only, no pith","½ tsp whole black peppercorns","2 garlic cloves","3 green onions, white and green parts, divided","6 oz ricotta cheese","1 oz whole milk","¼ tsp red pepper flakes              (optional)","2 tbsp extra virgin olive oil, divided","2 oz yellow squash, thinly sliced rounds","2 oz zucchini, thinly sliced rounds","6 oz cherry tomatoes, halved"]}],"id":"r348769","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-7NGnM3LdAW0\/XZVQ2IP2KBI\/AAAAAAAAdGg\/Rlb14s2fEmQpK6r7TUO66YTrTvh9XOM7wCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_ZAdfVf8MM9YgpRX3.png","title":"Summer Squash Flatbread","publishedAt":"2018-05-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"6 g","fat":"5 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"23 g","calories":"669 kJ \/ 160 kcal"},"usefulItems":"paper towel, baking sheets, parchment paper, pastry brush, rolling pin, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Add capers or sliced olives during last 10-12 minutes of baking."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","50m","12 pieces"]}